    <main>
        <section>
            <h2>Executive Summary</h2>
            <p>
                Social services agencies face increasing demands with limited resources. This manual explores how
                generative AI can alleviate administrative burdens, streamline operations, and improve crisis response,
                while ensuring ethical, human-centric service delivery.
            </p>
            <p>
                <strong>Highlights:</strong>
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>Ethical AI Use: Transparency, inclusivity, and data privacy.</li>
                <li>Crisis Response: National and regional hotline directories.</li>
                <li>AI Strategies: Automated forms, data analysis, and resource matching.</li>
                <li>Compliance: Guidelines for HIPAA and privacy laws.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Strategic Plan for Incorporating GenAI</h2>
            <p>
                Generative AI empowers agencies by automating tasks, analyzing data, and enhancing communication. Below
                are steps for adoption:
            </p>
            <ol>
                <li>Identify administrative tasks suitable for automation (e.g., data entry, report generation).</li>
                <li>Train staff on AI tools and ethical guidelines.</li>
                <li>Integrate AI for real-time resource matching and client communication.</li>
                <li>Conduct regular audits to monitor AI outputs and maintain ethical standards.</li>
                <li>Leverage AI for predictive analytics to anticipate service demands.</li>
            </ol>
        </section>

